.SH Version 3.0.1 (2014\-07\-16)
.PP
This release restores Mac OS X support and fixes a permalink generation bug.
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
GH\-13: 
.BR man (1) 
on Mac OS X could not display URLs.
.PP
The version of groff on Mac OS X is too old: it lacks the an\-ext.tmac
macro package that defines styles for email addresses and general URLs.
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ groff \-\-version
\&...
GNU grops (groff) version 1.19.2
GNU troff (groff) version 1.19.2
.fi
.RE
.PP
This patch drops those URL macros in favor of simpler angled brackets.
.PP
Thanks to Sorin Ionescu for reporting this issue in GH\-13:
\[la]https://github.com/sunaku/md2man/issues/13\[ra]
.IP \(bu 2
.BR md2man-html (1): 
cross references were escaped in heading permalink IDs.
.RE
.SH Version 3.0.0 (2014\-06\-22)
.PP
This release changes 
.BR md2man-html (1) 
heading permalinks to follow GitHub style:
unique, lowercase, and squeezed and stripped of HTML tags and non\-word chars.
In addition, it renames the \fB\fCmd2man\-xref\fR CSS class to \fB\fCmd2man\-reference\fR\&.
.PP
Please make sure to update any existing bookmarks and/or hyperlinks you may
have for jumping to specific locations in your HTML manuals after upgrading.
.SS Major:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Make permalink anchors on headings fully lowercase in 
.BR md2man-html (1).
.IP \(bu 2
Put permalinks on left & indicate target permalink in 
.BR md2man-html (1).
.IP \(bu 2
Make permalink anchors unique by appending a count in 
.BR md2man-html (1).
.IP \(bu 2
Rename \fB\fCmd2man\-xref\fR CSS class to \fB\fCmd2man\-reference\fR in 
.BR md2man-html (1).
